<div class="min-h-screen bg-(--crit-bg-page) text-(--crit-fg-primary) font-sans antialiased">
  <Layouts.site_header current_scope={@current_scope} />
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-10 pb-20 max-sm:px-4 max-sm:pb-12">
    <%!-- Hero --%>
    <section class="mt-16 mb-14 max-sm:mt-10 max-sm:mb-10">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-(--crit-brand) mb-3">
        Integrations
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold leading-tight tracking-tight mb-4 max-sm:text-3xl">
        Build a crit integration<span class="text-(--crit-brand)">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-(--crit-fg-secondary)">
        Any agent that can run a shell command and read a file can use crit.
        All integrations follow the same pattern &mdash; only deviate when
        your agent has a specific quirk that requires it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- What an integration is --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">What an integration is</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-5">
        An integration is a set of skill files that teach your agent how to drive crit.
        Every integration ships two skills:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <code class="text-sm font-mono text-(--crit-brand) shrink-0 mt-0.5">crit</code>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">The review loop</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Launch crit, block until the user finishes reviewing, read the
              review JSON, address comments, re-run crit for the next round.
              This is the skill that powers <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">/crit</code>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <code class="text-sm font-mono text-(--crit-brand) shrink-0 mt-0.5">crit-cli</code>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Headless CLI commands</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Teaches the agent about <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit comment</code>, <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit share</code>, <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit pull</code>/<code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">push</code>,
              the review file format, and comment resolution workflow.
              Auto-activates when the agent works with review files or crit commands.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
        Some agents need additional files &mdash; hooks, policies, commands, or plugins &mdash;
        but the two skills are the foundation. Keep them consistent with the existing
        integrations unless your agent genuinely requires something different.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- The review loop --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">The review loop</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-6">
        This is the core protocol every integration teaches. Your agent repeats
        these steps until the reviewer approves with zero comments.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <span class="text-(--crit-brand) font-mono text-sm font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0 select-none">
            1
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">Run crit</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              The agent runs
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
                crit &lt;file&gt;
              </code>
              or bare
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit</code>
              for a branch diff. The CLI auto-detects the review mode. It spawns a daemon, opens the browser, and <strong>blocks until the user clicks Finish Review</strong>.
              There is no separate listen or wait command &mdash; the crit process itself is the blocking gate.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <span class="text-(--crit-brand) font-mono text-sm font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0 select-none">
            2
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">Read the review file</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              When crit exits, it prints the path to a JSON review file. The agent
              reads it and finds three types of comments: review-level
              (<code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">r_</code>-prefixed),
              file-level, and line-level (with <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">start_line</code>/<code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">end_line</code>).
              Each comment may have a
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">quote</code>
              (selected text) and an
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">anchor</code>
              for locating content after edits.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <span class="text-(--crit-brand) font-mono text-sm font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0 select-none">
            3
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">
              Address comments and reply
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              For each unresolved comment, the agent makes the requested change, then replies:
            </p>
            <div class="mt-3 bg-(--crit-code-bg) rounded px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-fg-secondary) overflow-x-auto">
              crit comment --reply-to &lt;id&gt; --author 'AgentName' 'Fixed.'
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mt-3">
              For multiple replies, use
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">--json</code>
              for a single bulk call. The agent never passes
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">--resolve</code>
              &mdash; resolving is the reviewer's call.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5">
          <span class="text-(--crit-brand) font-mono text-sm font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0 select-none">
            4
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight mb-1">
              Re-run the same crit command
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              The agent runs the <strong>exact same</strong>
              <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit</code>
              command from step 1. The daemon is keyed by arguments &mdash; mismatched args
              spawn a new daemon instead of reconnecting. Crit signals round-complete,
              reloads with a diff of what changed, and blocks again. Repeat from step 2.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mt-5">
        Zero unresolved comments = approved. The agent stops the loop and proceeds with implementation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- How to build one --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Building your integration</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-6">
        All changes go in the
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit"
          class="text-(--crit-brand) hover:underline"
        >
          crit
        </a>
        repo. Here's what a PR looks like:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-brand) text-white text-xs font-bold shrink-0">
              1
            </span>
            Write the skill files
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed pl-7">
            Copy from an existing simple integration (like
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              integrations/qwen/
            </code>
            or <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">integrations/grok/</code>)
            and change the
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">--author</code>
            name. Keep the protocol identical &mdash; only adjust if your agent's
            skill discovery format or execution model genuinely requires it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-brand) text-white text-xs font-bold shrink-0">
              2
            </span>
            Add routing in
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              cli_install.go
            </code>
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed pl-7">
            Add an entry to
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              integrationMap
            </code>
            mapping your agent name to file destinations:
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">source</code>
            (path in the embedded
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">integrations/</code>
            dir), <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">dest</code>
            (project install path),
            and optionally
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">globalDest</code>
            if your agent's global config lives somewhere different.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-brand) text-white text-xs font-bold shrink-0">
              3
            </span>
            Regenerate hashes and update tests
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed pl-7">
            Run
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              go generate ./...
            </code>
            to update
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              integration_hashes_gen.go
            </code>
            (used by
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit check</code>
            for staleness detection). Update the snapshot test in <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">integration_routing_test.go</code>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-5 h-5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-brand) text-white text-xs font-bold shrink-0">
              4
            </span>
            Update the README
          </h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed pl-7">
            Add your agent to the table in
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              integrations/README.md
            </code>
            with install command, project path, and global path.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%!-- Agent-specific quirks --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">When to deviate</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Most agents only need the two skill files. Some need more because of how they
        discover and load configuration. Only add extra files when your agent requires them:
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) px-5 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Different global path</strong>
            &mdash;
            e.g. Pi uses
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              ~/.pi/agent/skills/
            </code>
            for global installs vs
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">.pi/skills/</code>
            for project. Set
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">globalDest</code>
            in the routing table.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) px-5 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Custom commands or hooks</strong>
            &mdash;
            Gemini CLI needs a
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">.toml</code>
            command file, a policy file, and a settings merge for hooks. These
            are unique to Gemini's plugin system.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) px-5 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>Plugin registration</strong>
            &mdash;
            OpenCode needs a TypeScript plugin and a
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              opencode.jsonc
            </code>
            entry. Aider needs a
            <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">
              .aider.conf.yml
            </code>
            entry. These have custom install logic.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) px-5 py-4">
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed">
            <strong>No global install</strong> &mdash;
            Windsurf only supports a single shared <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">global_rules.md</code>,
            so global install is rejected with a clear error.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mt-5">
        If none of these apply, keep it simple: two skill files and standard routing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- Example PRs --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Example PRs</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Real PRs in order of complexity. Start with a simple one as your template.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-3">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/pull/544"
          class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5 no-underline text-inherit hover:border-(--crit-fg-muted) transition-[border-color] duration-150"
        >
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-brand) font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">
            #544
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Grok Build</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Simple &mdash; two skill files, standard paths, no special config.
              Best starting template.
            </p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/pull/500"
          class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5 no-underline text-inherit hover:border-(--crit-fg-muted) transition-[border-color] duration-150"
        >
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-brand) font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">
            #500
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Qwen Code</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Simple &mdash; same pattern as Grok. Good second reference.
            </p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/pull/520"
          class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5 no-underline text-inherit hover:border-(--crit-fg-muted) transition-[border-color] duration-150"
        >
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-brand) font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">
            #520
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Pi Coding Agent</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Medium &mdash; different global path
              (<code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">~/.pi/agent/skills/</code> vs project <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">.pi/skills/</code>).
            </p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/pull/488"
          class="flex items-start gap-4 border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg bg-(--crit-bg-card) p-5 no-underline text-inherit hover:border-(--crit-fg-muted) transition-[border-color] duration-150"
        >
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-brand) font-bold mt-0.5 shrink-0">
            #488
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Gemini CLI</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
              Complex &mdash; skills + command file + policy + hook settings merge.
              Only needed because of Gemini's TOML-based plugin system.
            </p>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%!-- Install command --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">How install works</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-5">
        Once your integration is merged,
        <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit install</code>
        copies the embedded skill files to the right place. Two modes:
      </p>

      <div class="border border-(--crit-border) rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2.5 bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) border-b border-(--crit-border)">
          <div class="flex gap-1.5">
            <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-fg-muted) opacity-40"></div>
            <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-fg-muted) opacity-40"></div>
            <div class="w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full bg-(--crit-fg-muted) opacity-40"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="font-mono text-xs text-(--crit-fg-muted) ml-2">Terminal</span>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-(--crit-code-bg) p-6 font-mono text-sm leading-7 text-(--crit-fg-secondary)">
          <div class="mb-1">
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) select-none">$ </span><span class="text-(--crit-fg-primary)">crit install &lt;agent&gt;</span>
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) ml-4"># project install</span>
          </div>
          <div class="mb-1">
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) select-none">$ </span><span class="text-(--crit-fg-primary)">cd ~ && crit install &lt;agent&gt;</span>
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) ml-4"># global install</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) select-none">$ </span><span class="text-(--crit-fg-primary)">crit install all</span>
            <span class="text-(--crit-fg-muted) ml-4"># install all supported agents</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed">
        Safe to re-run. Existing files are skipped unless
        <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">--force</code>
        is passed.
        <code class="text-xs bg-(--crit-bg-elevated) px-1 py-0.5 rounded">crit check</code>
        detects stale integrations by comparing installed file hashes against the
        manifest baked into the binary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <%!-- Source link --%>
    <section class="mb-16 max-sm:mb-12 border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-4">Source</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) leading-relaxed mb-4">
        All integration files live in the crit repo:
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/tree/main/integrations"
          class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-(--crit-brand) hover:underline"
        >
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0">
            <path d="M2 2.5A2.5 2.5 0 014.5 0h8.75a.75.75 0 01.75.75v12.5a.75.75 0 01-.75.75h-2.5a.75.75 0 110-1.5h1.75v-2h-8a1 1 0 00-.714 1.7.75.75 0 01-1.072 1.05A2.495 2.495 0 012 11.5v-9zm10.5-1h-6a1 1 0 00-1 1v6.708A2.486 2.486 0 017.5 9h5V1.5z" />
          </svg>
          integrations/ &mdash; skill files for every supported agent
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/blob/main/cli_install.go"
          class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-(--crit-brand) hover:underline"
        >
          <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4 shrink-0">
            <path d="M4.72 3.22a.75.75 0 011.06 1.06L2.06 8l3.72 3.72a.75.75 0 11-1.06 1.06L.47 8.53a.75.75 0 010-1.06l4.25-4.25zm6.56 0a.75.75 0 10-1.06 1.06L13.94 8l-3.72 3.72a.75.75 0 101.06 1.06l4.25-4.25a.75.75 0 000-1.06l-4.25-4.25z" />
          </svg>
          cli_install.go &mdash; routing table and install logic
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <%!-- CTA --%>
    <section class="border-t border-(--crit-border) pt-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mb-2">
        Need help<span class="text-(--crit-brand)">?</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-(--crit-fg-secondary) mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        If your agent isn't supported yet or you run into issues building an integration,
        open an issue and we'll help you get it working.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/tomasz-tomczyk/crit/issues"
